title: Resist Being Average | Shelly Omilâdé Bell
description: This week's guest is Shelly Omilâdé Bell, the founder of Black Girl Ventures. Not only is she a computer scientist, but also a serial entrepreneur, a disruption strategist, and an inspirational speaker. Black Girl Ventures is a social enterprise that creates access to social and financial capital to black and brown women founders.
